  "prompt": "What guidelines are in place regarding passport photos in Canada?",
  "response": "The Canadian government has very specific guidelines for passport photos. Here's a breakdown of the key requirements:\n\n**Overall Requirements:**\n\n*   **Recent:** Photos must be taken within the last six (6) months.\n*   **Identical:** Submit two (2) identical photos with your application.\n*   **Professional Quality:** Taken by a commercial photographer. Home-printed photos are generally not accepted.\n*   **Paper Quality:** Printed on high-quality photographic paper.\n*   **Unaltered:** Photos must be clear, sharp, and in focus. Digital alterations or enhancements are not allowed.\n\n**Photo Specifications:**\n\n*   **Size:**\n    *   The finished photos must be **50 mm wide x 70 mm high (2 inches wide x 2 \u00be inches high).**\n    *   The **height of the face** (from chin to crown) must be between **31 mm (1 \u00bc inches) and 36 mm (1 7/16 inches).**\n    *   The **head must be centred** within the photo.\n\n*   **Background:**\n    *   Plain **white or light-coloured background**.\n    *   The background should be free of shadows or reflections.\n\n*   **Lighting:**\n    *   Uniform lighting with no shadows, glare, or reflections on the face or in the background.\n    *   Red eye must be corrected.\n\n*   **Pose and Expression:**\n    *   **Neutral facial expression.**\n    *   Eyes open and clearly visible.\n    *   Mouth closed.\n    *   Facing the camera squarely.\n    *   Both ears should be visible.\n    *   Head must not be tilted or turned.\n\n*   **Eyeglasses:**\n    *   Eyeglasses are generally **not allowed** anymore.\n    *   There is an exception for non-removable medical reasons. However, the eyeglasses must not obscure the eyes, and a signed explanation from a doctor is required.\n\n*   **Head Coverings:**\n    *   Head coverings are only permitted for religious beliefs or medical reasons.\n    *   They must not cast shadows on the face, and the full facial features (chin, nose, eyes, and forehead) must be clearly visible.\n\n*   **Children:**\n    *   The same rules apply to children, including infants.\n    *   For infants, the photo must be taken with the infant lying on a plain white or light-coloured sheet.  No one else should be in the photo, and there should be no shadows on the infant's face or the background.\n    *   Support behind the infant should not be visible.\n\n**Photographer's Responsibilities:**\n\n*   The photographer must provide their studio address and the date the photo was taken directly on **one** of the photos. This information must be stamped or legibly hand-written; stickers are not accepted.\n*   The photographer's information should not cover any part of the subject's face.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n\n*   **The Passport Program has the right to reject any photo that does not meet these specifications.**\n*   **Check the Canadian Passport Office website (Canada.ca) for the most up-to-date information and guidelines.**  Search for \"passport photo requirements.\" They occasionally update the rules.\n*   **Before you go to a photographer, it's a good idea to mention that you need passport photos and that you're aware of the Canadian passport photo requirements.** This will help ensure they take the photos correctly.\n*   **Bring a copy of the passport photo requirements with you to the photographer.** This can help avoid misunderstandings.\n\nBy following these guidelines carefully, you can help ensure that your passport application is processed smoothly. Good luck!\n",
